I'm 14. I come home from school every day, drop my backpack, and start up my PS5. It's a decent console, and I've pushed it to its limit. I've learned how to build, how to edit, how to aim, and how to survive on a controller, in lobbies full of sweats, with no second chances. And every night, I'm staying up late watching VODs, studying rotations, discovering how the professionals move and think. Not because I want to be like them but because I know I can be one of them.

But there's one thing holding me back: I need a PC.

Not due to the fact that I need to flex more FPS or less input lag but since I understand that with the proper hardware, I can at last compete at the highest level. I could start qualifying for tournaments. I could prove I'm not just another grinder with a dream I'm someone willing to make it happen. Someone who wants to use this to provide for my family and change my future.


I don't want a handout.

If I must prove myself serious, I'll 1v1 you. I will show you that I have the mechanics, mentality, and hunger. I am not playingâ€”I am training. Each session, each clutch, each lossâ€”it is all part of the grind.
